<h2 class="h2">The pricing tiers</h2>
<p class="body">Three tier patterns dominate in 2026:</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Individual / Pro tier ($20-$30/mo)</strong> — for solo operators or individual contributors. Covers most use cases.</li>
<li><strong>Team / Business tier ($30-$60/seat/mo)</strong> — adds team sharing, admin controls, often higher usage limits.</li>
<li><strong>Enterprise tier (custom pricing)</strong> — adds SSO, audit logs, dedicated support, custom data agreements. Usually $60-$200+/seat/mo at scale.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">What to actually budget</h2>
<p class="body">Most B2B mid-market companies should budget for the team tier — not enterprise. Enterprise pricing only becomes justified above 50-100 seats or when specific compliance requirements force it.</p>
<p class="body">For solo operators and small teams: start with the Pro tier. Upgrade to Team only when collaboration features become necessary (sharing prompts, admin controls, etc.).</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Total cost including ecosystem</h2>
<p class="body">Don't just budget the subscription. Real-world costs include:</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li>Subscription itself ($20-$200/seat depending on tier)</li>
<li>API costs if you're building custom workflows (variable)</li>
<li>Adjacent tools (orchestration, integrations) — $30-$200/mo</li>
<li>Human-time to configure and maintain — 2-8 hours/week</li>
</ul>
<p class="body">All-in budget for a small team running serious AI workflows: $200-$1,500/month total. ROI usually positive within 30-60 days.</p>
